      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h3>Activity</h3>\n<p>A <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">monomial</span> is an algebraic expression with exactly one term: \\(5x^2\\)</p>\n<p>A <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">binomial</span> is an algebraic expression with exactly two terms: \\(5x^2 + 6y^3\\)</p>\n<p>A <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">trinomial</span> is an algebraic expression with exactly three terms: \\(5x^2 + 6y^3 - 7c\\)</p>\n<p>Monomials, binomials, and trinomials are all different types of polynomials. A <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">polynomial</span> is a monomial or two or more monomials combined by addition or subtraction.</p>\n<p>Working with your partner, use the following Desmos activity to sort the polynomials below. Then enter your answers below to check your understanding.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://teacher.desmos.com/activitybuilder/custom/6305ad5c0b0550149c69a5b9?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\">Polynomial Sort by Type</a></p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n  <colgroup>\n    <col width=\"155\">\n  </colgroup>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(x^2\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(c + 4\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(mn\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(8d^2 + 3e - g\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(b - h\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(15\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(n^2 - 7f + ab\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(z\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol>\n      <li>Which of the polynomials are monomials? </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(x^2\\), \\(15\\), \\(z\\), \\(mn\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"2\">\n      <li>Which of the polynomials are binomials?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(c + 4\\), \\(b - h\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"3\">\n      <li>Which of the polynomials are trinomials?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(8d^2 + 3e - g\\), \\(n^2 - 7f + ab\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<p>The <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">degree of a polynomial</span> is the highest degree of all its terms.</p>\n<p>Working with your partner, use the following Desmos activity to sort the same polynomials by degree. Then enter your answers below to check your understanding.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://teacher.desmos.com/activitybuilder/custom/6305ab339f43391984989b39?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\">Polynomial Sort by Degree</a></p>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"4\">\n      <li>Which of the polynomials have a degree of 0?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(15\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"5\">\n      <li>Which of the polynomials have a degree of 1?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(c + 4\\), \\(b - h\\), \\(z\\), \\(mn\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"6\">\n      <li>Which of the polynomials have a degree of 2?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(x^2\\), \\(8d^2 + 3e - g\\), \\(n^2 - 7f + ab\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->"
    }
  ]
